cs.CR, cs.HC, cs.CY, cs.MM, cs.CV 

The paper deals with continuous authentication using behavioral biometrics extracted from touchscreen input. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) as it deals with authentication. Additionally, the paper also involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) as it studies the way users interact with touchscreens. The use of touch input as a behavioral biometric also has applications in cyberpsychology (cs.CY) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper also involves computer vision (cs.CV) as it proposes a set of touch features that can be extracted from raw touchscreen logs.
